Ross Hadley is the envy of all his friends after being put in charge of fitness for the Miss World contest.

Ross, 35, from London has been given the task of measuring just how fit all 126 Miss World contestants really are.

The father-of-two only landed his job as director of leisure at the Marriott County Hall in Westminster, London, eight months ago, but now his place of work is home to the entire Miss World cortege ahead of the pageant on December 14.

Ross Hadley is the envy of all his friends being put in charge of fitness for the Miss World contest. He is pictured with (from left to right) Miss Wales Alice Ford, 21, a molecular biology student from Cardiff, Miss Northern Ireland Rebekah Shirley, 19, a media student from Belfast, Miss Ireland Jessica Hayes, 21, a business student from Cork, Miss Scotland Ellie McKeating, 20, a film and media student from Stirling, and Miss England Carina Tyrell, 24, a senior student doctor from Cambridge 

